how did we first realize the earth was round?

00:01:03.543 --> 00:01:08.240
The Greeks first realized this 2500 years
ago, and spent hundreds of years attempting

00:01:08.240 --> 00:01:09.360
to explain it.

00:01:09.360 --> 00:01:14.160
First, mathematician Pythagoras looked at
the moon and discovered a curve in the line

00:01:14.160 --> 00:01:18.570
dividing light from shadow on its surface
-- called the terminator.

00:01:18.570 --> 00:01:20.840
A flat moon would have a straight line!

00:01:20.840 --> 00:01:22.160
The only explanation?

00:01:22.160 --> 00:01:24.040
The moon must be a sphere!

00:01:24.040 --> 00:01:28.390
Sometime later, Anaxagoras, while watching
the moon during an eclipse, realized the shadow

00:01:28.390 --> 00:01:31.390
covering the moon must be from the Earth!

00:01:31.390 --> 00:01:35.520
As that shadow is definitely curved, the Earth
must be round!

00:01:35.520 --> 00:01:40.480
And still later in about 350 BC, Aristotle
noted that star constellations, visible in

00:01:40.480 --> 00:01:43.220
Greece were hidden beyond the horizon in Egypt.

00:01:43.220 --> 00:01:48.310
His conclusion, yet again, was the Earth must
be a sphere, just like the moon!

00:01:48.310 --> 00:01:52.550
