00:01:59.760 --> 00:02:02.820
A Greek astronomer named Eratosthenes figured
it out.

00:02:02.820 --> 00:02:06.770
On the summer solstice, the sun reaches a
peak at the top of the sky.

00:02:06.770 --> 00:02:11.310
Eratosthenes went to two distant locations
in Egypt on the Solstice and measured the

00:02:11.310 --> 00:02:14.220
angles cast by the shadows in each place.

00:02:14.220 --> 00:02:18.710
Then, using some geometry he could calculate
the curvature of the Earth between those places!

00:02:18.710 --> 00:02:23.200
